It's only fair that I end 2013 with a review for Gary Danko, a place the wifey and I have been trying to visit for more than a year. On a random Monday, all the stars finally aligned (baby sitter, reservation, wife's birthday, etc.) and we found ourselves waiting for our table at Gary Danko. And waiting. And waiting. We waited a good 40 minutes for our table. The hostess was very apologetic and said people were lingering over dessert at their tables. To me, it seems somewhat predictable that people would linger after spending hundreds of dollars on a huge meal and certainly, a restaurant of this caliber should anticipate this kind of behavior of patrons. Once we finally go to our table, things picked up. We were offered an amuse bouche from the kitchen (a carrot ginger soup that was too heavy on the curry powder). The wifey and I placed our order (we both went with the four course) and were then offered a second amuse bouche. A fantastic buckwheat belini, topped with smoked salmon, creme fraiche, and caviar. I could've eaten a plate of those bad boys. But sadly, I only had one. For our dinner, we each ordered 4 courses and shared everything: 1) Crispy egg- This was a showstopper. A poached egg, fried in panko, on a bed of grits, frisee and mushrooms. I don't think I've ever anything this unique or delicious. 2) Loin of lamb- It was good lamb but it was kind of mild tasting, but it didn't really have the "lamb" taste. 3) Filet of beef- Also good but sadly, the potato gratin side was more memorable. 4) Flambed banana crepes- The tableside fire show is better than the crepes which were sort of just there. But the show? Fantastic. 5) Risotto with lobster- I had high hopes for this dish but the risotto was under seasoned, with very minimal lobster. 6) Roast Maine lobster- Great quality lobster (and a giant portion), with great mushrooms. 7) Duck breast- Again, the flavor was mild. Even after someone told me it was supposed to be lemon pepper flavored, I couldn't find the lemon or pepper flavor. However, the duck hash was heavenly! 4) Chocolate souffle- The biggest disappointment of the night. This is the most recommended item in all the Yelp reviews and it was just sort of there. The souffle was obviously well prepared but lacking in the chocolate flavor department. I could've used a whole lot more of the sauces they poured on top! At the end of our meal, they brought over a small plate of mini dessert bites plus a lemon mousse cake for the wife's birthday. We took a small bite of the lemon mousse cake and agreed it was actually better than the desserts we'd ordered! The complimentary desserts were definitely nice touches after a giant meal and we ended up taking them both home. And then, they handed us a pumpkin cream cheese muffin for the morning after so we definitely went home stuffed and with plenty of treats for the next day. All of the portions were generous and definitely larger than the ones we've had at other fine dining establishments. We both agreed we could've done the three course and been full (but then we wouldn't have gotten to try as many things)! Before going, I'd read the reviews and I saw everyone raving about the service but honestly, the service didn't stand out. Sure, the waiter knew about the preparation of various dishes in detail but to me, that's expected at a place that's charging $100 a person. The water glasses and bread plates were refilled timely but again, that's almost expected. The one exceptional part was hearing the waiter talk about the 50 cheeses on the cheese cart in detail. That man knew his cheese! Overall, it's a nice experience and definitely a destination meal in SF but I'm not sure it's worth repeating.

    6) Roast Maine lobster- Great quality lobster (and a giant portion), with great mushrooms.

    Gary Danko sets the bar really high. Since GD I have gone to numerous Michelin rated restaurants and the service and food here are top of the line. Service especially is phenomenal. Since our table wasn't ready for our reservation and we had to wait 15min my date and I were given two complimentary appetizers. They and the food we ordered were delicious.
    And even though we were embarrassed to ask servers to take our picture at this nice restaurant, the servers were more than happy to do it.
